Diagnosis.
Apex of fastigium rounded (
Fig. 8
); fore femur with 1 dorsal inner subapical spur (in addition to 1 dorsal inner apical spur, 
Fig. 25
); male X th abdominal tergite without gap between hooks (
Fig. 49
); male epiproct distal margin strait (
Fig. 49
); female subgenital plate triangular, acute (
Fig. 89
